This season I have seen so many offensive linemen score a touchdown. 
I've been trying to see for the past 20 years, and if there is no mistake with the label position, this is the most productive year for the big man!

#nflverse #nfl @MitchSchwartz71 https://t.co/5pLO8wfht7

Well, it was a great game!

Data: #nflverse https://t.co/ZJosO0E48P

King of the Fourth, King of the Fourth! Despite an up-and-down season, Matthew Stafford leads all quarterbacks in fourth-quarter EPA (min. 100 dropbacks), while the AFC West is well represented in the top five. #nflverse https://t.co/fhQknTyrDN

Robby Anderson has 101 targets this season but somehow just 469 receiving yards. He has also run the 7th most routes in the NFL.

His total receiving EPA is -27 (from #nflverse). No other player is below 0.

This is truly unbelievable stuff. https://t.co/5pvBP4xZAx
